Program: Discovery
Title: Could mosquitos transmit the malaria vaccine?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwrf
Last Broadcast Date: 04 November 1996
A progress report on the latest antimalarial and transmission-blocked vaccines. Some of the work aimed at eradicating malaria is looking at delivering a gene back to mosquitoes which would actually vaccinate the humans they bite. Also in the programme, plans for a trip to the moon for the year 2000, the microscope that defies expectations and a strange monkey with a strange face. Presenter unknown. Show less